articles.title: 22000-foot volcano summit is home to Earth's highest-dwelling vertebrates, study confirms - Livescience.com
articles.description: Mummified mice found atop volcanoes in South America have long hinted that rodents forage on peaks as tall as 22,000 feet, but it turns out mice permanently live at these extreme heights.
articles.content:
A live leaf-eared mouse (Phyllotis vaccarum) was spotted on the summit of Llullaillaco volcano on the border between Argentina and Chile. (Image credit: adrian gallardo via Getty Images)
